  abstract={This paper examines the environmental impact of machine learning model training, focusing on its carbon footprint. The authors argue that although the computational cost of training large-scale models has increased significantly, improvements in hardware efficiency, data center optimization, and the growing use of renewable energy sources will lead to a plateau and eventual reduction in emissions. The study highlights trends in energy consumption, discusses the role of more efficient algorithms, and emphasizes the importance of sustainable AI practices. Overall, it suggests that while AI development is energy-intensive, industry and technological shifts are likely to mitigate long-term environmental impact.},
